{"name":"House Scion","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.SyGFQAUWO5lYWqmd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Forget the noble families of Galifar—the real power lies in the hands of the dragonmarked houses. You are a member of one of those houses, and though power comes with any number of responsibilities, you welcome your house duties as a reasonable price to pay for the social, political, economic, and magical power to which you are heir.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Arcana, Common Knowledge, Dragonmark Focus, Persuasion, Traditions</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Dragonmark), Charismatic, House Scion, Rich, Filthy Rich</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections</p>","_id":"YCwpwUDMgligJqHI"}
