{"name":"Paladin","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.w8MXUYWW2zi3Phyx"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Like clerics, Paladins are the champions of the churches, most notably the Church of the Silver Flame and, in some cases, select churches of the Sovereign Host. Paladins follow an exalted life and are held to a higher standard than even clerics. Clerics can fall to corruption and still retain their abilities, but paladins are above the corruption that can infect a church and adhere to the highest ideals of their faiths.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Athletics, Faith, Fighting, Healing, Persuasion, Riding</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance:</strong> Code of Honor, Vow</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Miracles), Charismatic</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Any combat edge</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Any leadership edge</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Guardian, Knight</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Bolster, Provoke, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Champion</p>","_id":"a5VWuXuF3pwiyQ4U"}
{"name":"Barbarian","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OwFGvHEjm9cHtgDD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Even in these enlightened times, primal warriors linger on the edges of Khorvaire. Fearsome fighters, defined by durability, speed, instinct, and the ability to channel oneself into a physical frenzy. Traditionally barbarians are savage champions of cultures seen as primitive, relying on force and fury in place of sophisticated techniques.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Intimidation, Notice, Riding, Stealth, Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Berserk, True Berserker, Brawny, Brute</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Any combat edge</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Monster Hunter</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Humiliate, Provoke, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Danger Sense, Liquid Courage</p>","_id":"cRG4aNyXu3dikgkf"}
{"name":"Skills","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_evsfcpx4ty","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Creation","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Skills</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.More Skill Points]{More Skill Points} Setting Rule is in effect, therefore all characters start with 15 points to buy skills during character creation. A skill that&rsquo;s below the linked attribute (noted in parentheses beside the skill name) is cheaper to increase than one that&rsquo;s at or above it. See <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Character Creation Summary]{Character Creation}</strong> and <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}.</strong></p>\n<p>Core skills are marked with a <span class=\"red-text\">red star</span>, and start at d4 for@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{player characters}.</p>\n<p>Characters can attempt skills they don&rsquo;t have but it&rsquo;s more difficult. See<strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Unskilled Attempts}</strong>.</p>\n<h2>Skill changes in Savage Eberron from Savage Worlds</h2>\n<p>The following skills from <cite>Savage Worlds</cite> are not available in <cite>Savage Eberron.</cite></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"red-text\">Academics</span> has been renamed to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}</li>\n<li><span class=\"red-text\">Driving</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"red-text\">Electronics</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"red-text\">Hacking</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"red-text\">Occult</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"red-text\">Piloting</span>&nbsp;has been updated to be used with elemental bound vehicles.</li>\n<li><span class=\"red-text\">Repair</span> has been updated to be used with artifice and warforged.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<figure class=\"figure table-figure\">\n<figcaption class=\"figure-heading\">Skill Summaries</figcaption>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skills</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Animal Handling]{Animal Handling} (Spirit):</span> Skill with handling and training animals.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcan]{Arcana} (Smarts):</span> Knowledge about the spells, artifacts, magical traditions, etc.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold core-skill\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Athletics]{Athletics} (Agility):</span> Overall athletic coordination and ability. Climbing, jumping, balancing, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} (Smarts):</span> Strategy, tactics, and understanding military operations. A key skill in Mass Battles.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} (Agility):</span> Ability to sail or pilot a boat, ship, or other watercraft.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold core-skill\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} (Smarts):</span> General knowledge of a character&rsquo;s world.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Cosmology]{Cosmology} (Smarts):</span> Knowledge of the planes, their properties, inhabitants, and manifest zones.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Crafting]{Crafting} (Smarts):</span> The ability to control, steer, and operate ground vehicles.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} (Agility):</span> Skill in armed and unarmed combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Gambling]{Gambling} (Smarts):</span> Skill and familiarity with games of chance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing} (Smarts):</span> The ability to treat and heal Wounds and diseases, and decipher forensic evidence.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (Spirit):</span> A character&rsquo;s ability to threaten others into doing what she wants.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language} (Smarts):</span> Knowledge and fluency in a particular language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore} (Smarts):</span> Knowledge of History, Ages, Legends, literature, song, poetry, etc.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold core-skill\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Notice]{Notice} (Smarts):</span> General awareness and perception.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} (Spirit):</span> Singing, dancing, acting, or other forms of public expression.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold core-skill\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Persuasion]{Persuasion} (Spirit):</span> The ability to convince others to do what you want.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} (Agility):</span> Skill with maneuvering elemental bound vehicles.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion} (Smarts):</span> Knowledge about religions, rites, traditions and symbols.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} (Smarts):</span> The ability to fix mechanical gadgets, vehicles and warforged.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research} (Smarts):</span> Finding written information from various sources.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} (Agility):</span> A character&rsquo;s skill in mounting, controlling, and riding a tamed beast.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Science]{Science} (Smarts):</span> Knowledge of scientific fields such as biology, chemistry, geology, engineering, etc.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} (Agility):</span> Precision with any type of ranged weapon.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold core-skill\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Stealth]{Stealth} (Agility):</span> The ability to sneak and hide.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} (Smarts):</span> How to find food, water, or shelter, and tracking.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} (Smarts):</span> Insulting or belittling another. Almost always done as a Test.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Traditions]{Traditions} (Smarts):</span> Knowledge of court ettiquette and courtesies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} (Agility):</span> Sleight of hand, pickpocketing, lockpicking, and other typically shady feats.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skills for Arcane Backgrounds</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Dragonmark Focus]{Dragonmark Focus} (Spirit):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Dragonmark)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Druidism]{Druidism} (Spirit):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Druidism)]{Arcane Background (Druidism)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} (Spirit):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Miracles)]{Arcane Background (Miracles)}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Focus]{Focus} (Spirit):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Gifted)]{Arcane Background (Gifted)}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Herbalism]{Herbalism} (Smarts):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Herbal Alchemy)]{Arcane Background (Herbal Alchemy)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Magecraft]{Magecraft} (Smarts):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Magecraft)]{Arcane Background (Magecraft)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} (Smarts):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Psionics)]{Arcane Background (Psionics)}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Song Magic]{Song Magic} (Smarts):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Song Magic)]{Arcane Background (Song Magic)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} (Smarts):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Arcane Background (Magic)}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Wand Magic]{Wand Magic} (Smarts):</span> The arcane skill for&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Wandslinger)]{Arcane Background (Wandslinger)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Weird Science]{Weird Science} (Smarts):</span> The arcane skill for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Weird Science)]{Arcane Background (Weird Science)}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"dFLGuPgWblZxGuyo"}
