{"name":"Wizard","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.23nhljaxcjJ23SWE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>As a wizard, you&rsquo;re an arcane scientist and, like any scientist, you could be diligent, eccentric, or even stark-raving mad. Among the other magically inclined, you have every reason to be proud of your talents. Bards? Stage magicians obsessed with fame. Sorcerers? Freaks who won the genetic lottery. You earned your power. You&rsquo;re a bona fide genius and it&rsquo;s unlikely that anyone will soon forget how bright your brilliance burned, especially if you go out in a fireball of glory.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Arcana, Common Knowledge, Cosmology, Language, Lore, Science, Spellcasting</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Magic), Arcane Resistance, Improved Arcane Resistance, Linguist, University Trained</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Channeling, Concentration, Power Surge, Wizard</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Familiar, Scholar</p>","_id":"doBUxN3jTVMfxTDr"}
