age-eberron-edges.Attune Arcane Weapon]</td>\n<td>S, Artificer</td>\n<td>The artificer gains +1 bonus to attack and damage with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Channeling]{Channeling}</td>\n<td>S, AB</td>\n<td>Reduce Power Point cost by 1 with a raise on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Activation]{Activation} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Extra Effort]{Extra Effort}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Gifted), Focus d6</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Focus]{Focus} by +1 for 1 Power Point or +2 for 3 Power Points.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Finely Tuned]</td>\n<td>S, Artificer, Sm d8, Crafting d8</td>\n<td>Reduce the cost of creating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Focus]</td>\n<td>S, AB, Sp d6, arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>If the wizard is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} from failing to cast a spell, they get an automatic roll to unshake at &ndash;2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Focus]</td>\n<td>H, Focus</td>\n<td>If the wizard is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} from failing to cast a spell, the get an automatic roll to unshake.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Miracles), Faith d6</td>\n<td>Add +1 to +4 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} for each Power Point spent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Imbue Item]</td>\n<td>S, AB (Magecraft), Magecraft d6</td>\n<td>Spend 3 Power Points to create a device that replicates another power.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Miracles), Faith d6</td>\n<td>Add +1 to +4 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} for each Power Point spent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Mentalist]{Mentalist}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Psionics), Psionics d6</td>\n<td>+2 to opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.New Powers]{New Powers}</td>\n<td>N, AB</td>\n<td>Your character knows two new powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Spell Finesse]</td>\n<td>N, AB, Arcana d8, arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strong Caster]</td>\n<td>S, AB, Sm d6, Sp d6, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 1 point of casting penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Strong Caster]</td>\n<td>H, Concentration</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of casting penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Wizard]{Wizard}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Magic), Spellcasting d6</td>\n<td>Spend 1 extra Power Point to change a spell&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trapping}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Professional Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Ace]{Ace}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Character may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} damage for his vehicle and ignores up to 2 points of penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Acrobat]{Acrobat}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll on acrobatic @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Athletics]{Athletics} attempts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Combat Acrobat]{Combat Acrobat}</td>\n<td>S, Acrobat</td>\n<td>&minus;1 to hit with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{ranged and melee attacks}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Assassin]{Assassin}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Fighting d6, Stealth d8</td>\n<td>+2 to damage foes when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or assassin has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Boarder]</td>\n<td>N, Athletics d8+, Boating d6+</td>\n<td>All @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Athletics]{Athletics} rolls on ropes are made with a +2 bonus. Receives a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} if he is the first boarding an enemy vessel.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Entertainer]</td>\n<td>N, Performance d8</td>\n<td>+1 to any two \"bard\" skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Explorer]</td>\n<td>N, V d6, Survival d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} and to resist the effects of heat and cold enviroments.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Familiar]</td>\n<td>N, AB (Magic) Arcana d8</td>\n<td>The mage acquires an animal familiar.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Guardian]</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Fighting d6, Notice d6</td>\n<td>Attacks aimed at a chosen charge are rolled against the guardian.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Holy Adept]</td>\n<td>N, AB (Miracles), Faith d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>The adept adds a d4 to unarmed attacks and can activate a power on themselves as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Investigator]{Investigator}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d8, Research d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research} and certain types of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Notice]{Notice} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Jack-Of-All-Trades]{Jack-Of-All-Trades}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d10</td>\n<td>Gain d4 in a skill (or d6 with a raise) until replaced.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Knight]</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, St d8, v d8, Fighting d8, Riding d8</td>\n<td>The knight is gifted with the tools of his trade. He also gains a +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when dealing with good causes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Storyteller]</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, Persuasion d8</td>\n<td>The storyteller rolls d8's for Glory rolls instead of d6's.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Legendary Storyteller]</td>\n<td>H, Master Storyteller</td>\n<td>The storyteller gains a d8 Glory for each raise after the first.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monster Hunter]</td>\n<td>S, Sp d6</td>\n<td>The hero is immune to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks of one type of creature.&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Mr Fix It]{Mr. Fix It}</td>\n<td>N, Repair d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Repair]{Repair} rolls, half the time required with a raise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Necromancer]</td>\n<td>N, AB (magic or Miracles) Sp d8, arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>May cast @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Zombie]{Zombie} as a Novice. Additional, reduce the cost of casting and extend the duration.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Necromancer]</td>\n<td>V, Necromancer</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Zombie]{Zombies} raised by Necromancer gain an extra die in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and one skill of his choice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rope Monkey]</td>\n<td>S, A d8, Athletics d10</td>\n<td>The sailor can swing among the rigging to move around a ship or canopy. They may also make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Athletics]{Athletics} roll if they fall to take half damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Scholar]{Scholar}</td>\n<td>N, Research d8</td>\n<td>+2 to any one &ldquo;knowledge&rdquo; skill.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skald]</td>\n<td>N, Performance d6</td>\n<td>+2 to any one \"skald\" skill.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Soldier]{Soldier}</td>\n<td>N, S d6, V d6</td>\n<td>Strength is one die type higher for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Minimum Strength]{Min Str}. Reroll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls when resisting environmental @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tinkerer]</td>\n<td>S, Crafting d8, Magecraft d10</td>\n<td>The artificer may craft an item that adds a +1 bonus to a relevant @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{trait} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Thief]{Thief}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Stealth&nbsp;d6, Thievery d6</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Athletics]{Athletics} rolls made to climb, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Stealth]{Stealth} in urban environments.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Woodsman]{Woodsman}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, Survival d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Stealth]{Stealth} in the wilds.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Racial Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Adamantine Body]</td>\n<td>N, Warforged</td>\n<td>Start with +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bladedancer]</td>\n<td>N, Elf, A d8, Fighting d8, Two-Fisted</td>\n<td>Make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{run} roll, and get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack at everything in his path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extra Shifter Ability]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter</td>\n<td>Gains one additional shifting ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healing Factor]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter, V d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll} on any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} when ending shifting.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Overload Metabolism]</td>\n<td>N, Warforged, A d8, Str d8</td>\n<td>Once per session make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to repair one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}. two on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Reduce @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} one die type for 10 minutes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Primal Fury]</td>\n<td>S, Half-orc or ORc, Berserk</td>\n<td>May spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to activate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Primal Fury]</td>\n<td>V, Primal Fury, Sp d8</td>\n<td>No penalty to end rage, and the hero will not hit an ally on a Critical Failure with her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psicrystal]</td>\n<td>N, Kalashtar, SB (Psionics), Sm d8</td>\n<td>Allows the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Kalashtar]{Kalashtar} to have a fragment of thier personality placed into a srystalline construct with some abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psiforged Body]</td>\n<td>N, Warforged, AB (Psionics)</td>\n<td>This adds 5 Powers Points for a Psionic Warforged.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reactive Shifting]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter, Quick</td>\n<td>Shifters can shift as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} even when not on their turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Running Throw</td>\n<td>S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Str d8, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>The hero moves at least half their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} and throws a weapon may increase their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{range} by 2/4/8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scamper]</td>\n<td>S, Halfling, A d8</td>\n<td>Opponents larger than the hero subtract 1 from their attack rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Scamper]</td>\n<td>V, Scamper</td>\n<td>Opponents get no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{gang up} on the hero.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shieldwall]</td>\n<td>S, Hobogoblin, Block</td>\n<td>The hero can add his shield modifier to an adjacent ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shifter Stamina]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter</td>\n<td>The adventurer is immune to nonlethal damage and the effects of fatigue while they are shifted.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sunder]</td>\n<td>S, Dwarf</td>\n<td>The adventurer ignores 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 2 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sunder]</td>\n<td>V, Sunder</td>\n<td>The hero ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 4 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.War Cry]</td>\n<td>S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Social Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Bolster]{Bolster}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>May remove @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable} state after a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Common Bond]{Common Bond}</td>\n<td>WC, N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>The hero may freely give her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to others.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Connections]{Connections}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Contacts provide aid or other favors once per session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Humiliate]{Humiliate}</td>\n<td>N, Taunt d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Menacing]{Menacing}</td>\n<td>N, See Text</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Provoke]{Provoke}</td>\n<td>N, Taunt d6</td>\n<td>May &ldquo;provoke&rdquo; foes with a raise on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} roll. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rabble-Rouser]{Rabble-Rouser}</td>\n<td>S, Spirit d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a Medium Blast Template with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Reliable]{Reliable}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Retort]{Retort}</td>\n<td>N, Taunt d6</td>\n<td>A raise when resisting a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} attack makes the foe @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Streetwise]{Streetwise}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and criminal networking.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Strong Willed]{Strong Willed}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts or Spirit}-based @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Iron Will]{Iron Will}</td>\n<td>S, Brave, Strong Willed</td>\n<td>The bonus now applies to resisting and recovery from powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Work The Room]{Work The Room}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, roll a second die when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Supporting} via @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Persuasion]{Persuasion} and apply result to additional ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Work the Crowd]{Work the Crowd}</td>\n<td>S, Work the Room</td>\n<td>As above, but up to twice per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Weird Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Beast Bond]{Beast Bond}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>The hero may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} for animals under her control.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Beast Master]{Beast Master}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Animals like your hero and he has a pet of some sort. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Champion]{Champion}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>+2 damage vs. supernaturally evil creatures.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Chi]{Chi}</td>\n<td>V, Martial Warrior</td>\n<td>Once per combat, reroll failed attack, make enemy reroll successful attack, or add +d6 to unarmed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Notice]{Notice} roll at +2 to sense ambushes or similar events.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Healer]{Healer}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing} rolls, magical or otherwise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Liquid Courage]{Liquid Courage}</td>\n<td>N, V d8</td>\n<td>Alcohol increases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} a die type and ignores one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; &ndash;1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility, Smarts}, and related skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Scavenger]{Scavenger}</td>\n<td>N, Luck</td>\n<td>May find a needed item once per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Storm Chaser]</td>\n<td>N, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during storms. Recieve extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Symbiont Mastery]</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6</td>\n<td>Recieve +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} in battle of wills with sybionts. With symbiont attached, +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]</td>\n<td>N, Sm d8, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during Contact. Recieve extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Legendary Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Followers]{Followers}</td>\n<td>WC, L</td>\n<td>The hero has five followers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Professional]{Professional}</td>\n<td>L, Max Trait</td>\n<td>The character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Expert]{Expert}</td>\n<td>L, Professional in Trait</td>\n<td>The character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Master]{Master}</td>\n<td>WC, L, Expert in Trait</td>\n<td>The character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Wild Die} is a d10 with a chosen @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Enchant]</td>\n<td>L, Enchant</td>\n<td>Allows the artificer to craft major artifacts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick}</td>\n<td>WC, L</td>\n<td>The character gains a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} sidekick.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Tough As Nails]{Tough As Nails}</td>\n<td>L, V d8</td>\n<td>The hero can take four @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Tougher Than Nails]{Tougher Than Nails}</td>\n<td>L, Tough as Nails, V d12</td>\n<td>The hero can take five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Weapon Master]{Weapon Master}</td>\n<td>L, Fighting d12</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} increases by +1 and Fighting bonus damage die is d8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Master of Arms]{Master of Arms}</td>\n<td>L, Weapon Master</td>\n<td>Parry increases another +1 and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{bonus damage} die is d10.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"vjjucQp5WeUPPsve"}
{"name":"Priest/Acolyte","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.87vhPveKV00IKJfp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>It’s important to understand that in Eberron, not all priests can wield divine energies. A priest provides spiritual guidance to a community and congregation and they don’t need magic to do this. An acolyte is a servant in training to a particular faith.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Common Knowledge, Cosmology, Healing, Persuasion, Religion</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance:</strong> Vow</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Miracles), Charismatic</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Command, Command Presence, Fervor, Fanaticism, Inspire, Natural Leader</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Holy/Unholy Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Monster Hunter, Scholar</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Bolster, Rabble-Rouser, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Champion, Healer</p>","_id":"wdb3NwKaLFMMvpXB"}
{"name":"What Are Character Concepts?","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.dscZLSyEHmodbYAq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>With all the options<span class=\"ILfuVd\"><span class=\"hgKElc\">—</span></span>between skills, attributes, and edges<span class=\"ILfuVd\"><span class=\"hgKElc\">—it can be challenging to understand how to express a character concept or idea for your character. This can be particularly difficult without character class concepts like in the oldest RPG in the world. <br></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ILfuVd\"><span class=\"hgKElc\">Below are a list of a bunch of <em>possible</em> character ideas and concepts and how to build them in Savage Worlds. These are not exact builds for a particular character or concept. But these lay out the kinds of skills and edges that you might want to consider taking to build the kind of character that you are looking for. </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ILfuVd\"><span class=\"hgKElc\">Remember these are just <em>suggestions</em>. This is after all your character. Build the character that you are looking for that will be fun for you.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ILfuVd\"><span class=\"hgKElc\">Here is something to consider with these concepts and any character in Savage Worlds since it does not have a clear path light character classes. Character classes are very clear paths for your characters to take. Since there are none, come up a clear concept and long term direction that you would like to take your character. You can even bring in character ideas from books or movies or other stories. Then look at the skills and edges and then build out a plan to create that character.</span></span></p>","_id":"wp0Ujzy1dusmln9p"}
{"name":"Goblin","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.p9Bxarupnmiw6UST"},"cf":{"id":"temp_evvs3sf1aoa","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Races","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Goblin</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The goblinoid species&mdash;goblins, hobgoblins, and bugbears&mdash;were once the dominant civilization in Khorvaire, with the goblinoid Empire of Dhakaan ruling the continent for thousands ofyears. It was crippled by a long conflict with the daelkyr and their aberrant armies; even though the daelkyr were defeated, the seeds of madness took root in the empire and tore it apart. Today there are four primary goblinoid cultures in Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>Amongst the most areas of Khorvaire goblins are at best second class citizens that are often nothing more than scavengers. Among the <em>dar</em> or goblinoid races, goblins are known as the <em>golin'dar</em>, the \"quick people\", known as crafters, skilled labor, and excellent scouts. Not knowing any better, when humans came to Khorvaire they named the goblinoid people after the most prolific breeders, goblins.</p>\n<h3>City Goblins</h3>\n<p>Goblins dwell in most o f the major cities of the Five Nations. When humans first came to Khorvaire, they enslaved many goblins and built their cities on the foundations of Dhakaani ruins. Galifar ended the practice of slavery, and these goblins are now citizens of the Five Nations. Gifted goblins can be found in all walks of life, and goblins served in the armies of the Five Nations during the Last War.</p>\n<h3>The Heirs of Dhakaan</h3>\n<p>Though the Dhakaani Empire defeated the alien daelkyr, the war left seeds ofcorruption strewn throughout the empire. As Dhakaan began to fall, a number of generals and governors gathered their forces and retreated into shelters deep within the earth, determined to preserve their civilization until the Empire could finally be restored. After thousands of years, their descendants have finally emerged, competing among themselves to determine which leader deserves the imperial crown. Once this is settled, they will turn to the conquest of Darguun and Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>The Dhakaani are far fewer in number than the&nbsp;<em>ghaal'dar</em>; they had to carefully limit their population in the underground vaults they've dwelled in for the past age. However, they have held onto the martial discipline and techniques that allowed their ancestors to dominate the continent. Their weaponsmiths are superior even to the artificers of House Cannith, and they are experts in the working of adamantine and other exotic metals. Anyone who presumes to look down upon goblinoids should be surprised by the skills of the Dhakaani.</p>\n<p>The Heirs of Dhakaan are an agnostic society and don't have clerics, paladins, or druids. Their focus is on martial excellence, and their spiritual leaders are bards, who tell tales of past glory. Among the Dhakaan, goblinoids work together. Hobgoblins are the strategists and commanders, typically having the skills of fighters, bards, or rangers. Bugbears cultivate a focused battle rage and are typically barbarians. Goblins are largely artisans and laborers, but exceptional goblins join the khesh'dar (\"silent folk\"), learning the skills of rogues, monks, or rangers. The khesh'dar spread agents across the Five Nations, and one can never know when a city goblin might turn out to be an assassin.</p>\n<p>As an adventurer from a Dhakaani clan, consider why are you working with the other player characters? Are you a scout gathering information? Are you searching for allies to defeat a rival clan, or to support your own unlikely bid for the Imperial throne? Are you an exile? If so, do you hope to regain your position, or have you abandoned your ties to the Dhakaani?</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Agile:</strong> Goblins are naturally quick and agile. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Athletics]{Athletics} instead of a d4. This increases their maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.npGSR7Ru0Jl4LUXq]{Athletics} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>Diminutive: </strong>Goblins average only about three and a half feet tall, reducing their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) by 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language}: </strong>Goblins start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Languages]{Goblin}.</li>\n<li><strong>Low Light Vision: </strong>Goblin eyes have become accustomed to the darkness in Khyber. They ignore penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim or Dark illumination} (but not Pitch Darkness).</li>\n<li><strong>Sneaky:</strong> Goblins are naturally stealthy. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.★ Stealth]{Stealth} skill instead of a d4. This increases their maximum Stealth to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>Tricksy Fighter: </strong>Goblins do anything to win a fight. They add +2 to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Tests]{Tests} during combat.</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"text-align: center; padding-top: 20px;\"><img src=\"modules/savage-eberron-rules/assets/art/goblin.webp\" alt=\"Goblin with a toad on his head.\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-rules/assets/art/goblin.webp","_id":"x99c87TBrIFSioJf"}
{"name":"Bounty Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.G4Pzh2XyhAw9EiYp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The most reputable bounty hunters in Khorvaire are members of House Tharashk’s Finders Guild. Still others might operate independently to avoid the strict policies and procedures imposed by House Tharashk, but competition with the Finder’s Guild is stiff.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Healing, Intimidation, Shooting, Survival, Thievery</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Luck</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Calculating, Level Headed</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Escape Artist, Explorer, Investigator, Jack-of-all-Trades</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections, Streetwise</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Danger Sense, Scavenger</p>","_id":"yXH88z6vWI3IbI2h"}
{"name":"Monk","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.hUQGZcxPSlD3LK6T"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y896zqjqkx","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Beginning with a foundation of mental and physical discipline, a monk channels energy to force an impossible action to become possible, from moving with superhuman speed to striking with fists of flame. The monk focuses power within them and becomes a conduit with the strictest discipline.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Athletics, Fighting, Faith or Psionics, Notice, Religion, Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Miracles or Psionics), Fleet-Footed, Quick</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Counterattack, Improved Counterattack, Free Runner, Martial Artist, Martial Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Holy/Unholy Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Acrobat, Guardian, Holy Adept</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Chi, Danger Sense</p>","_id":"yYlb8S8tvnVsixIk"}
